1
00:00:57,359 --> 00:00:58,159
After taking the medication,

2
00:00:58,280 --> 00:01:00,079
you may experience dizziness, headaches,

3
00:01:00,240 --> 00:01:02,280
vomiting, diarrhea, and rashes.

4
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:03,799
But don't worry too much.

5
00:01:04,079 --> 00:01:05,239
These are all temporary.

6
00:01:05,799 --> 00:01:07,519
Don't put too much pressure on yourself.

7
00:01:20,920 --> 00:01:21,879
Lin Fei'er and I

8
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:24,239
are already in the past.

9
00:01:25,519 --> 00:01:27,359
Whether she shows up or not,

10
00:01:28,359 --> 00:01:29,879
it won't affect my decision.

11
00:01:33,359 --> 00:01:35,280
That's what I wanted to say last time.

12
00:01:37,480 --> 00:01:39,599
I hope you won't let it bother you.

13
00:01:42,359 --> 00:01:43,159
Dr. Jiang,

14
00:01:43,480 --> 00:01:45,400
what's our relationship now?

15
00:01:45,959 --> 00:01:47,519
Do you think I'd mind?

16
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:56,640
Do you know

17
00:01:56,719 --> 00:01:58,840
a typical sign of a guilty conscience?

18
00:01:59,959 --> 00:02:01,439
It's exactly how you're acting right now.

19
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:05,560
What do I have to feel guilty about?

20
00:02:19,479 --> 00:02:20,120
Who is it?

21
00:02:20,759 --> 00:02:21,479
Big Mouth.

22
00:02:25,879 --> 00:02:26,800
Just pretend I was never here.

23
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:40,879
I was worried you'd be lonely,

24
00:02:41,199 --> 00:02:42,680
so I came to keep you company.

25
00:02:43,439 --> 00:02:44,240
How are you, Dr. Jiang?

26
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:45,159
Does your face still hurt?

27
00:02:46,479 --> 00:02:47,520
Took you so long to open the door.

28
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:49,319
Hiding someone in here, aren't you?

29
00:02:55,319 --> 00:02:56,680
Dr. Jiang, what a lucky man you are!

30
00:02:57,199 --> 00:02:57,879
Look,

31
00:02:58,159 --> 00:02:59,000
who's come to see you?

32
00:03:00,199 --> 00:03:01,199
Dr. Jiang!

33
00:03:01,719 --> 00:03:02,280
Auntie Jiang.

34
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:03,000
We heard about you,

35
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:05,319
and we couldn't help but worry,

36
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:06,879
so we came together to check on you.

37
00:03:07,639 --> 00:03:08,919
These are vegetables we grew ourselves.

38
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:11,080
Eat plenty and get well soon.

39
00:03:11,639 --> 00:03:12,879
Save some for Dachun.

40
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:15,240
Our son loves the vegetables you grow.

41
00:03:15,599 --> 00:03:16,919
Look how stingy you are.

42
00:03:17,319 --> 00:03:18,879
These are for our son.

43
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:21,240
I'm giving them all to him, aren't I?

44
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:22,120
I-I-I really can't, I can't.

45
00:03:22,199 --> 00:03:23,080
- Take it. - I can't.

46
00:03:23,199 --> 00:03:24,560
We won't bother you anymore. We're off.

47
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:25,360
Auntie Jiang!

48
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:26,639
I really can't accept this, I...

49
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:27,800
It's not against the rules.

50
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:29,400
This is Auntie Jiang's token of goodwill.

51
00:03:29,879 --> 00:03:30,599
Just accept it.

52
00:03:30,719 --> 00:03:31,520
We've got plenty here.

53
00:03:32,719 --> 00:03:33,360
That's right.

54
00:03:33,599 --> 00:03:34,400
Let me see what good things

55
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:35,759
are in these two bags.

56
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:40,639
Dr. Jiang,

57
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:42,159
did you know we were coming

58
00:03:42,319 --> 00:03:44,439
and prepared a royal feast in advance?

59
00:03:56,560 --> 00:03:57,439
Look at him.

60
00:03:57,599 --> 00:03:58,159
You should learn from him.

61
00:03:58,319 --> 00:03:59,520
I will. I'll start once we get home.

62
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:01,280
Dr. Jiang,

63
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:03,159
you've really kept this hidden.

64
00:04:03,919 --> 00:04:05,159
Not only are you amazing at surgery,

65
00:04:05,439 --> 00:04:06,560
your cooking skills are top-notch too.

66
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:08,439
How is it? Sweet enough?

67
00:04:41,519 --> 00:04:42,120
Here.

68
00:04:43,879 --> 00:04:44,879
You guys start. I'll hit the restroom.

69
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:46,160
Don't worry about us. Hurry back.

70
00:05:03,279 --> 00:05:03,879
Dr. Tang,

71
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:06,199
Such a shame you couldn't make it today.

72
00:05:06,319 --> 00:05:08,360
This spread is absolutely divine.

73
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:20,199
Dr. Jiang,

74
00:05:20,879 --> 00:05:22,240
You should text your girlfriend back.

75
00:05:22,959 --> 00:05:24,040
Don't keep her waiting and worried.

76
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:26,519
I'm single.

77
00:05:28,240 --> 00:05:29,879
Being single is great!

78
00:05:30,199 --> 00:05:31,240
For someone who's a doctor,

79
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:33,959
being single means more time and energy

80
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:35,360
to devote to your work,

81
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:36,839
to benefit your patients.

82
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:39,920
Every one of you is so ambitious.

83
00:05:40,519 --> 00:05:41,199
Not like me.

84
00:05:41,879 --> 00:05:44,439
Just drifting through the day in a daze.

85
00:05:45,839 --> 00:05:46,560
Do you know

86
00:05:47,079 --> 00:05:48,879
why I originally chose to become a nurse?

87
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:50,920
At eighteen, because of my malocclusion,

88
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:52,800
the flight attendant program rejected me.

89
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:54,680
Out of spite, I switched to dentistry.

90
00:05:54,959 --> 00:05:56,000
You've told this story 800 times.

91
00:05:56,199 --> 00:05:56,680
Aren't you tired of it?

92
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:59,279
Mind your business. I wasn't telling you.

93
00:06:00,399 --> 00:06:01,560
Before I got into this field,

94
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:03,279
my parents always told me,

95
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:04,959
"Being a dentist is great.

96
00:06:05,079 --> 00:06:06,839
High income, light workload."

97
00:06:07,199 --> 00:06:09,000
But once I got into it, I realized

98
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:10,959
how often we swallow the bitter pill,

99
00:06:11,399 --> 00:06:12,720
and hardly anyone even knows.

100
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,600
A dentist is still a doctor, after all.

101
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:16,120
Others finish a bachelor's in four years,

102
00:06:16,319 --> 00:06:17,839
we study five, like clinical med students.

103
00:06:17,959 --> 00:06:19,199
Others graduate and start working,

104
00:06:19,399 --> 00:06:21,480
while we pursue master's and PhDs,

105
00:06:21,639 --> 00:06:22,879
Residency, specialist training,

106
00:06:23,279 --> 00:06:24,720
write papers, face Promotion review,

107
00:06:24,839 --> 00:06:25,600
and grind for seniority.

108
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:27,160
After finally making it this far,

109
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:28,439
you'd think we could stand on our own.

110
00:06:28,839 --> 00:06:29,519
But what happens?

111
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:30,680
Patients don't understand us,

112
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:32,000
and competition among peers is fierce.

113
00:06:33,759 --> 00:06:35,920
In any other job, if you make a mistake,

114
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:37,920
there might still be a chance to fix it.

115
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:40,199
But once we doctors slip up,

116
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:41,480
what's lost

117
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:43,639
could be a human life,

118
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:45,480
an entire family.

119
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:49,079
So, look,

120
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:50,879
think about what happened the other day.

121
00:07:51,399 --> 00:07:53,759
We just wanted the best for the patient,

122
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:54,519
but in the end,

123
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:56,319
we were not only branded as quacks,

124
00:07:56,399 --> 00:07:58,079
but risked occupational exposure too.

125
00:07:58,759 --> 00:07:59,720
You think we're not frustrated?

126
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:00,519
How could we not be?

127
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:01,759
How could we not be?

128
00:08:05,199 --> 00:08:06,160
In this world,

129
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:08,120
no path is ever smooth sailing.

130
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:13,079
The moment I stepped into medical school,

131
00:08:14,199 --> 00:08:16,079
I was ready to bear it all.

132
00:08:19,399 --> 00:08:20,399
If this time

133
00:08:21,959 --> 00:08:22,959
I really am infected,

134
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:26,560
then it's my fate. I accept it.

135
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:29,079
But I don't want what happened to me

136
00:08:30,199 --> 00:08:31,399
to make you regret

137
00:08:34,399 --> 00:08:35,840
becoming a medical professional.
